## 7. Power Automate — Flow 1: Document Enrichment Pipeline

### Overview

**Trigger:** When a new file is created in Library 1  
**Purpose:** Validate, enrich, and publish document to Library 2

---

### 7.1 Create the Flow

1. Go to **Power Automate** → **Create** → **Automated cloud flow**
2. Name: `HR — Document Enrichment Pipeline`
3. Trigger: `SharePoint — When a file is created (properties only)`
4. Configure trigger:
   - Site Address: `[Your HR Copilot Knowledge site URL]`
   - Library Name: `HR Staging`

---

### 7.2 Action 1 — Initialize Variables

Add a **Parallel Branch** with the following variable initializations (run together):

```
Initialize variable — varFileExtension
  Name: varFileExtension
  Type: String
  Value: (empty)

Initialize variable — varExtractedText
  Name: varExtractedText
  Type: String
  Value: (empty)

Initialize variable — varAIDescription
  Name: varAIDescription
  Type: String
  Value: (empty)

Initialize variable — varAIKeywords
  Name: varAIKeywords
  Type: String
  Value: (empty)

Initialize variable — varConfidence
  Name: varConfidence
  Type: String
  Value: (empty)

Initialize variable — varConfidenceReason
  Name: varConfidenceReason
  Type: String
  Value: (empty)

Initialize variable — varIsDuplicate
  Name: varIsDuplicate
  Type: Boolean
  Value: false
```

---

### 7.3 Action 2 — Set Pipeline Status to Processing

```
SharePoint — Update file properties
  Site Address: [Site URL]
  Library Name: HR Staging
  ID: [ID from trigger]
  Pipeline_Status: Processing
```

---

### 7.4 Action 3 — Get File Content

```
SharePoint — Get file content
  Site Address: [Site URL]
  File Identifier: [Identifier from trigger — use the ID field]
```

---

### 7.5 Action 4 — Set File Extension Variable

```
Set variable — varFileExtension
  Value: 
  toLower(last(split(triggerOutputs()?['body/{FilenameWithExtension}'], '.')))
```

---

### 7.6 Action 5 — File Type Validation (Condition)

```
Condition:
  varFileExtension — is not equal to — pdf
  AND
  varFileExtension — is not equal to — docx
  AND
  varFileExtension — is not equal to — doc
  AND
  varFileExtension — is not equal to — xlsx
```

**If TRUE (unsupported file type) — Rejection Branch A:**

```
Step A1 — SharePoint: Update file properties
  Pipeline_Status: Rejected
  Rejection_Reason: Unsupported file type. Please upload PDF or DOCX only.

Step A2 — SharePoint: Move file
  Current site: [Site URL]
  Current library: HR Staging
  File to move: [Full path from trigger]
  Destination site: [Site URL]
  Destination path: /HR Staging/Rejected

Step A3 — SharePoint: Create item (Rejected Documents Register)
  Title: [FilenameWithExtension from trigger]
  Rejection_Date: utcNow()
  Rejection_Reason: Unsupported file type
  Rejection_Type: Wrong File Type
  Submitted_By: [Created By from trigger]
  Resolution_Status: Pending

Step A4 — Office 365 Outlook: Send an email
  To: [Created By Email from trigger]
  Subject: Document upload rejected — @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{FilenameWithExtension}']}
  Body:
    Hi @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{Author/DisplayName}']},

    Your document could not be processed.

    Document: @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{FilenameWithExtension}']}
    Reason: File type not supported.

    Please re-upload your document as a PDF or DOCX file.

    If you need assistance, please contact the HR systems team.

    This is an automated message.

Step A5 — Terminate
  Status: Succeeded
```

**If FALSE — continue to next step**

---

### 7.7 Action 6 — Extract Text from Document

```
AI Builder — Extract text from file
  File: [File Content from Action 3]

→ Output stored in expression for next step:
  outputs('Extract_text_from_file')?['text']
```

```
Set variable — varExtractedText
  Value: outputs('Extract_text_from_file')?['text']
```

---

### 7.8 Action 7 — Scanned PDF / Empty Document Check (Condition)

```
Condition:
  length(variables('varExtractedText')) — is less than — 500
```

**If TRUE (likely scanned or empty) — Rejection Branch B:**

```
Step B1 — SharePoint: Update file properties
  Pipeline_Status: Needs Review
  Rejection_Reason: Document appears to be a scanned PDF or contains no readable text.

Step B2 — SharePoint: Move file
  Destination path: /HR Staging/Needs-Review

Step B3 — SharePoint: Create item (Rejected Documents Register)
  Title: [Filename]
  Rejection_Type: Scanned PDF
  Rejection_Reason: Fewer than 500 characters extracted. Likely scanned PDF.
  Resolution_Status: Pending

Step B4 — Office 365 Outlook: Send an email
  To: [Created By Email]
  Subject: Document needs attention — @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{FilenameWithExtension}']}
  Body:
    Hi @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{Author/DisplayName}']},

    Your document could not be automatically processed.

    Document: @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{FilenameWithExtension}']}
    Reason: The document appears to be a scanned PDF or contains no 
    readable text. Our system requires text-based documents to generate 
    metadata automatically.

    Please re-upload a text-based PDF or DOCX version of this document.
    If this document must remain as a scanned PDF, please contact the 
    HR systems team for manual processing.

    This is an automated message.

Step B5 — Terminate
  Status: Succeeded
```

**If FALSE — continue**

---

### 7.9 Action 8 — Duplicate Detection

```
SharePoint — Get items
  Site Address: [Site URL]
  List Name: Agent Knowledge
  Filter Query: 
    Document_Title eq '@{triggerOutputs()?['body/{FilenameWithExtension}']}'
    and Pipeline_Status eq 'Published'
  Top Count: 1
```

```
Condition:
  length(outputs('Get_items')?['body/value']) — is greater than — 0
```

**If TRUE (duplicate found):**

```
Step C1 — Set variable: varIsDuplicate = true

Step C2 — SharePoint: Update file properties (Library 1)
  Pipeline_Status: Duplicate Review
  Rejection_Reason: A published document with this name already exists in the knowledge base.

Step C3 — SharePoint: Create item (Rejected Documents Register)
  Rejection_Type: Duplicate
  Resolution_Status: Pending

Step C4 — Office 365 Outlook: Send an email
  To: [Created By Email]
  CC: [Document_Owner from trigger if different]
  Subject: Duplicate document detected — @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{FilenameWithExtension}']}
  Body:
    Hi @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{Author/DisplayName}']},

    A published version of this document already exists in the 
    knowledge base.

    Document: @{triggerOutputs()?['body/{FilenameWithExtension}']}

    If this is an updated version, please:
    1. Locate the existing document in the Agent Knowledge library
    2. Set its status to Archived in Library 1 first
    3. Then re-upload your new version

    If you believe this is an error, please contact the HR systems team.

Step C5 — Terminate
  Status: Succeeded
```

**If FALSE — continue**

---

### 7.10 Action 9 — AI Builder Enrichment Prompt

```
AI Builder — Create text with GPT using a prompt
```

**Prompt text (paste exactly):**

```
You are an HR document metadata assistant. Your job is to analyse 
HR documents and generate accurate, searchable metadata.

Analyse the following document text and return ONLY a valid JSON 
object. No preamble, no explanation, no markdown formatting, 
no code fences. Return the raw JSON object only.

{
  "description": "A 2-3 sentence plain English summary of what this document covers, 
                  who it applies to, and what actions or information it provides. 
                  Begin with the document type and primary topic.",
  "keywords": "A comma-separated list of 10-15 keywords and phrases that an employee 
               would realistically type when searching for this document. Include 
               synonyms and related terms.",
  "confidence": "HIGH, MEDIUM, or LOW based on how clearly the document text 
                 allowed you to generate accurate metadata",
  "confidence_reason": "One sentence explaining your confidence rating. 
                        Write 'N/A' if confidence is HIGH."
}

Rules:
- Description must be factual, not promotional
- Keywords must reflect real employee search behaviour
- If the document text is fragmentary, heavily formatted, or unclear, 
  set confidence to LOW and explain why
- If document text appears to be a form with mostly blank fields, 
  set confidence to LOW

DOCUMENT TEXT (first 5000 characters):
@{substring(variables('varExtractedText'), 0, min(5000, length(variables('varExtractedText'))))}
```

> Store the response in a variable: `varAIRawResponse`

---

### 7.11 Action 10 — Parse AI Response

```
Data Operations — Parse JSON
  Content: @{outputs('Create_text_with_GPT_using_a_prompt')?['text']}
  Schema:
  {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "description": { "type": "string" },
      "keywords": { "type": "string" },
      "confidence": { "type": "string" },
      "confidence_reason": { "type": "string" }
    }
  }
```

```
Set variable — varAIDescription
  Value: [description from Parse JSON]

Set variable — varAIKeywords
  Value: [keywords from Parse JSON]

Set variable — varConfidence
  Value: [confidence from Parse JSON]

Set variable — varConfidenceReason
  Value: [confidence_reason from Parse JSON]
```

---

### 7.12 Action 11 — Confidence Check (Condition)

```
Condition:
  varConfidence — is equal to — LOW
```

**If TRUE:**

```
Step D1 — SharePoint: Update file properties (Library 1)
  Pipeline_Status: Needs Review
  AI_Confidence: Low
  AI_Confidence_Reason: [varConfidenceReason]

Step D2 — Office 365 Outlook: Send an email
  To: [Document_Owner from trigger]
  CC: HR Admin mailbox
  Subject: Document requires review before publishing
